# Google Calendar to Discord Sync - Crontab Examples
#
# Edit your crontab with: crontab -e
# View current crontab: crontab -l
#
# Cron format: MIN HOUR DAY MONTH WEEKDAY COMMAND
# Example: 0 9 * * * /path/to/command  # Runs at 9:00 AM every day

# ============================================================
# Example 1: Run every 30 minutes
# ============================================================
*/30 * * * * /opt/gcal-to-discord/examples/cron/gcal-sync.sh

# ============================================================
# Example 2: Run every hour at minute 0
# ============================================================
0 * * * * cd /opt/gcal-to-discord && uv run gcal-to-discord --once

# ============================================================
# Example 3: Run at specific times (9 AM, 1 PM, 5 PM on weekdays)
# ============================================================
0 9,13,17 * * 1-5 /opt/gcal-to-discord/examples/cron/gcal-sync.sh

# ============================================================
# Example 4: Run every 15 minutes during business hours (8 AM - 6 PM)
# ============================================================
*/15 8-18 * * * /opt/gcal-to-discord/examples/cron/gcal-sync.sh

# ============================================================
# Example 5: Run twice daily (morning and afternoon)
# ============================================================
0 8,17 * * * cd /opt/gcal-to-discord && uv run gcal-to-discord --once

# ============================================================
# Example 6: Run with custom environment file
# ============================================================
0 * * * * cd /opt/gcal-to-discord && uv run gcal-to-discord --once --env-file /etc/gcal-to-discord/.env

# ============================================================
# Example 7: Run with output to specific log file
# ============================================================
*/30 * * * * cd /opt/gcal-to-discord && uv run gcal-to-discord --once >> /var/log/gcal-discord/sync.log 2>&1

# ============================================================
# Cron Schedule Reference
# ============================================================
# MIN   HOUR  DAY   MONTH WEEKDAY
# 0-59  0-23  1-31  1-12  0-7 (0 or 7 is Sunday)
#
# Special characters:
# *     = any value
# ,     = list of values (1,3,5)
# -     = range of values (1-5)
# /     = step values (*/15 = every 15)
#
# Examples:
# */5 * * * *     = Every 5 minutes
# 0 */2 * * *     = Every 2 hours
# 0 9-17 * * 1-5  = Every hour from 9 AM to 5 PM, Monday-Friday
# 0 0 * * 0       = Every Sunday at midnight
# 0 12 1 * *      = 12 PM on the 1st of every month
